The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Good Morning
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Good Morning
      Hello It's Monday , July 5 , 2010                    
	Whats on    Emergency services like hospitals, blood banks, medicine shops and hearse vans.    Calcutta High Court and all lower courts.     Metro Railway to run trains. Eastern and South Eastern Railway will operate long distance and suburban trains provided there is no obstruction.     Both state and central government offices will remain open.    Several IT offices with US-based clients to remain closed but others will try to ferry in employees before 6am. IT sector has not been exempted from the purview of the bandh. Cops have provided all companies with helpline numbers where employees can call in case of any obstruction.     
	Whats off    Most taxis, buses and autos.    Private airlines will not operate flights between 6am and 6pm. Around 40 flights will be cancelled, around 25 morning flights will be preponed and a similar number in the afternoon to be postponed. Air India to operate morning flights on schedule. Some international flights to operate on schedule.    Most educational institutions.     Most malls will remain closed till 6pm. Forum and City Centre I and II may open at 5pm. Multiplexes will open at 5pm.                                                                                                                                                  
